<p>So I'm using the com.fasterxml.jackson readValue method, which works perfectly fine. It takes in a json String and a POJO that is populated and saved to obj:</p>  <pre><code>Object obj = mapper.readValue(myJsonString, MyPojo.class); </code></pre>  <p>For some reason, if I create a util class that does the same thing, I get an IO exception when I use the readValue() method.  When I print c, i get: "class models.UserProfile" . When I print out c.getClass(), I get "class java.lang.class". Is there something wrong with the way I'm passing the class?</p>  <pre><code>    public static Object deserialize(String s, Class c) throws JsonParseException, JsonMappingException, IOException {      Object obj = mapper.readValue(s, c);     return obj; } </code></pre>